  <description type="morphology">Shrubs or trees, 1–5 m. Leaves mostly well spaced, 20–90 mm. Pedicels mostly long. Flowers: sepals 8–12 mm; petals 12–18 mm. Follicles 2–9, 15–20(–32) mm. Seeds 18–22, 2–3 mm diam. 2n = 24.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering Feb–May.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Dry rocky slopes, often in canyons, coastal scrub and chaparral, on igneous or volcanic substrates;</description>
  <description type="elevation">50–500 m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Calif.; Mexico (Baja California).</description>
